# MTF Confluence Dashboard – Installation Guide
**10-second setup | 100% free | Works on all TradingView accounts (Basic included)**

---

## Step 1: Get the Code
1. Go to the GitHub repository:
   https://github.com/WiseManAlgo/MTF-Confluence-Dashboard
2. Open the main script file: `mtf-confluencet.pine`
3. Click the **Copy raw content** button (top-right of the code box) to copy all code to your clipboard.

## Step 2: Open TradingView Pine Editor
1. Go to [TradingView](https://www.tradingview.com) and open any chart.
2. At the **bottom** of the screen, click the **Pine Editor** tab.

## Step 3: Paste & Activate
1. Delete any existing code in the Pine Editor.
2. Paste the code you copied from GitHub.
3. Click **Add to Chart** (or press `Ctrl + Enter` / `Cmd + Enter`).

## Done!
Your MTF Confluence Dashboard will appear immediately on your chart.

---

## Notes
- No repainting
- No lookahead bias
- No premium subscription required
- Automatically updates when you refresh the code

---

## Troubleshooting
If the indicator does not load:
1. Make sure you pasted **all code** correctly.
2. Check for empty lines or missing text at the top/bottom.
3. Re-copy and re-paste the full code.

